    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment: Accepted. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is acknowledged; however, the remaining factors collectively provide sufficient evidence that the FEA framework accurately predicts ASTM F1717 compression-bending behavior for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct within the defined COU. The quantitative output comparison demonstrates all QoIs within pre-established acceptance bounds across N=11 constructs at two independent laboratories. The assessment team accepts the model for its intended regulatory use with the noted limitation on test condition coverage.",
